article.headline: Penn 21, Bucknell 3
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- Touchdown runs by Brad Blackmon and Lyle Marsh helped Penn to a strong second half in a 21-3 win over Bucknell on Saturday in a game dominated by defense early. The only pass by Matt Hamscher was a 5-yard score to Luke Deluca for the lone points in the first half and a 7-0 Penn (3-3) lead. The offenses were stagnant in the third quarter, but in the final minute, Bucknell's Bryce Robertson picked off a pass by John Hurley at the Penn 27-yard line. The Bison (2-2) settled for a field goal. Later, Bucknell's Tyler Smith fumbled and it was recovered by Fred Craig. Two plays later, Blackmon ran in from four yards and made the score 14-3. Marsh capped the scoring with his 3-yard run. Hurley in his first career start completed 14 of 27 passes for 148 yards. The Bucknell defense had three interceptions and Greg Jones recorded 11 tackles.
